# pyenv
#   For a library or binary, you wish to ignore their .python-version file.
#   For a project, you should check it in.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to check Pipfile.lock into source control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don't work, or even
#   fail to install all dependencies. In that case, add Pipfile.lock to .gitignore.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to check poetry.lock into source control.
#   Poetry's lock file is platform-independent, so it should be checked in.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to check pdm.lock into source control.
#pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

